    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1970-09-20T13:54:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1970-09-20T13:54:00-05:00" n="277"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d277">
                <head>277. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Embassy in Lebanon</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d277fn1">Source: National Archives, <gloss
                            target="#t_RG1">RG</gloss> 59, Central Files 1970–73, PS 7–6 JORDAN.
                        Secret; Immediate. Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_KAI1"
                            >Killgore</persName>; cleared in <gloss target="#t_NEAARN1"
                            >NEA/ARN</gloss>; and approved by <persName corresp="#p_SJJ1"
                            >Sisco</persName>. It was repeated Immediate to Amman, and to Bern,
                        Bonn, Geneva, London, and Tel Aviv.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1970-09-20T18:54:00+00:00">September 20, 1970,
                        1854Z</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>154423. Ref: Beirut 7937.<note n="2" xml:id="d277fn2">Telegram 7937 from Beirut,
                        September 21, included six demands made by the <gloss target="#t_PFLP1"
                            >PFLP</gloss> regarding the hostage situation. The Embassy informed
                        Zayn, who served as an intermediary with the <gloss target="#t_PFLP1"
                            >PFLP</gloss>, that he should pass on to <gloss target="#t_ICRC1"
                            >ICRC</gloss> all information he wished to send to the U.S. Government.
                        Additionally, the Embassy told Zayn that the U.S. Government had not
                        accepted any <gloss target="#t_PFLP1">PFLP</gloss> proposals. (Ibid.)</note>
                    Subject: <gloss target="#t_PFLP1">PFLP</gloss> Hostages.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Department entirely agrees that Embassy has scrupulously avoided giving
                        Zayn and <gloss target="#t_PFLP1">PFLP</gloss> any valid reason for assuming
                        that Embassy agreement to pass on <gloss target="#t_PFLP1">PFLP</gloss>
                        terms for release of hostages somehow implies <gloss target="#t_USG1"
                            >USG</gloss> acceptance of those terms. Yet they appear to <pb
                            facs="0802" n="769" xml:id="pg_769"/> be making this assumption,
                        probably without being honestly convinced of <gloss target="#t_USG1"
                            >USG</gloss> acceptance but rather as a negotiating tactic which they
                        reason might serve to split five-power united front.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>We believe time has now rpt now come to break off contact with Zayn in
                        matter of hostages. You may be as diplomatic as you wish with him consistent
                        with his fully understanding that Embassy wishes no rpt. no longer receive
                        or transmit <gloss target="#t_PFLP1">PFLP</gloss> conditions.</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>Embassy’s contacts with Zayn served a useful purpose during period when
                        movement on hostages in Amman was frozen because of civil war in city.
                        However, security situation there has improved, <gloss target="#t_ICRC1"
                            >ICRC</gloss> representatives have proceeded to Amman and negotiations
                        on spot may be expected to resume. In these circumstances, Amman is proper
                        place and <gloss target="#t_ICRC1">ICRC</gloss> is proper forum for
                        receiving information from and carrying on negotiations with the <gloss
                            target="#t_PFLP1">PFLP</gloss>.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RWP1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Rogers</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
